item.title: Terraform IaC
item.description: Table of Contents Introduction Reference links Terraform project structure SourceCode RootModule ChildModule Terraform module deployment Introduction Terraform is an open-source, infrastructure as code, software tool created by HashiCorp. Users define and provide data center infrastructure using a declarative configuration language known as HashiCorp Configuration Language (HCL), or optionally JSON. terraform init: Download and install Terraform plugins and remote modules, init workspace terraform plan: Dry run terraform code terraform apply: Create/update infrastructure resources defined in the code terraform destroy: Delete infrastructure resources Reference links: www.
